{"lemma":"فَرْعَيْ","slug":"فَرْعَيْ","root":"ف.ر.ع","root_slug":"ف-ر-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ف-ر-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"فَرْع","root":"فرع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":18},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n33612","","n33616","n33617"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ascend, to mount, to overtop; to descend"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to excel, to surpass, to outdo"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to branch out"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to derive, to deduce"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to slaughter for offering, to sacrifice (a فَرَع (faraʕ))","examples":[{"text":"فَقَالَ رَجُلٌ مِنَ النَّاسِ «يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ الْعَتَائِرُ وَٱلْفَرَائِعُ؟» قَالَ «مَنْ شَاءَ عَتَرَ وَمَنْ شَاءَ لَمْ يَعْتِرْ وَمَنْ شَاءَ فَرَّعَ وَمَنْ شَاءَ لَمْ يُفَرِّعْ فِي الْغَنَمِ أُضْحِيَتُهَا»","english":"Then a man among the people said: “O Messenger of Allah, what about the goat slaughter and goat firstling slaughter?“ He said: Whoso wishes to offer a goat may do so, and whoso does not wish to may not. Whoso wishes to offer a firstling may do so, and whoso does not wish to may not. And with regard to sheep, a sacrifice should be made.”"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"branch, twig, shoot, limb"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"top of a branch; top"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"section, subdivision"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"derivation, derivative"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of فَرَعَ (faraʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"branching out"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ramification; corollary"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"branch office","examples":[{"text":"البَنْكُ لَدَيْهِ العَدِيدُ مِنَ الفُرُوعِ الْمَنْتَشِرَةِ فِي مُخْتَلِفِ الْمُدُنِ وَالْمَنَاطِقِ.","english":"The bank has many branches spreading across various cities and regions."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"branch line"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"branch wire"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"long hair"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"firstling of a camel or goat or sheep","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"فِي كُلِّ سَائِمَةٍ فَرَعٌ تَغْذُوهُ مَاشِيَتُكَ حَتَّى إِذَا ٱسْتَحْمَلَ","english":"On every pasturing animal there is a firstling that your cattle feeds until it becomes capable of carrying a load."},{"text":"فَقَالَ رَجُلٌ مِنَ النَّاسِ: «يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ، الْعَتَائِرُ وَٱلْفَرَائِعُ؟» قَالَ: «مَنْ شَاءَ عَتَرَ وَمَنْ شَاءَ لَمْ يَعْتِرْ، وَمَنْ شَاءَ فَرَّعَ وَمَنْ شَاءَ لَمْ يُفَرِّعْ فِي الْغَنَمِ أُضْحِيَتُهَا.»","english":"Then a man among the people said: “O Messenger of Allah, what about the goat slaughter and goat firstling slaughter?“ He said: Whoso wishes to offer a goat may do so, and whoso does not wish to may not. Whoso wishes to offer a firstling may do so, and whoso does not wish to may not. And with regard to sheep, a sacrifice should be made.”"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"louse","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fa.ra.ʕa/","/far.ra.ʕa/","/fa.raʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33612","headword_ar":"فَرَعَ","root":"frE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, overtopped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surpassed in height"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tallness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"this seems to be the primary signification]. It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakaAdu yaforaEu","text_ar":"يَكَادُ يَفْرَعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsa TuwlFA","text_ar":"النَّاسَ طُولًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was, near to overtopping the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"surpassing them in tallness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEa fiY qawomihi","text_ar":"فَرَعَ فِى قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAla","text_ar":"طَالَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He surpassed in tallness among his people"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfrE","text_ar":"افرع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEa Alqawoma","text_ar":"فَرَعَ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEotu qawomiY","text_ar":"فَرَعْتُ قَوْمِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwEN","text_ar":"فُرُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, superior to the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, superior to my people"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in beauty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goodliness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEa","text_ar":"فَرَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAHibahu","text_ar":"صَاحِبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, superior to his companion; he excelled him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"brE","text_ar":"برع"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also 5.] ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEa","text_ar":"فَرَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TK [as is indicated in the K, and, in the former of the two senses here following,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwEN","text_ar":"فُرُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also, said in the TA to be syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SuEuwdN","text_ar":"صُعُودٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]), (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, O)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ascended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he descended:"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus having two contr. significations: (O, K, TA:) or, accord. to IAar, it has the former meaning, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfrE","text_ar":"افرع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has the latter meaning: (TA: [but see what follows:]) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEotu Aljabala","text_ar":"فَرَعْتُ الجَبَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aljabali","text_ar":"فِى الجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I ascended the mountain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"far~aEotuhu","text_ar":"فَرَّعْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, * K, *) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taforiyEN","text_ar":"تَفْرِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aljabali","text_ar":"فِى الجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"far~aEotu","text_ar":"فَرَّعْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I descended the mountain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiyhi","text_ar":"فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaEotu","text_ar":"اَفْرَعْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O, K:) or, as IB says, on the authority of A 'Obeyd,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Aljabali","text_ar":"فِى الجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfrE","text_ar":"افرع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ascended the mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu","text_ar":"مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AfrE","text_ar":"افرع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he descended it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEotu raA^osahu biAlEaSaA","text_ar":"فَرَعْتُ رَاْسَهُ بِالعَصَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, * TA, *) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaraEotuhu","text_ar":"قَرَعْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaroEN","text_ar":"قَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O;) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I smote his head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assailed it, smiting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealawotuhu","text_ar":"عَلَوْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, * TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihaA","text_ar":"بِهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DarobFA","text_ar":"ضَرْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the staff,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick"},{"kind":"text","text":"], and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAls~ayofi","text_ar":"بِالسَّيْفِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the sword"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEotu farasiY biAll~ijaAmi","text_ar":"فَرَعْتُ فَرَسِى بِاللِّجَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, *) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I pulled in my horse by the bridle and bit, to stop him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEotu bayonahumaA","text_ar":"فَرَعْتُ بَيْنَهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumo","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I interposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intervened as a barrier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between them two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"restrained"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them two,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made peace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effected a reconciliation, between them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fr~E","text_ar":"فرّع","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona Alqawomi","text_ar":"بَيْنَ القَوْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taforiyEN","text_ar":"تَفْرِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made a separation, and interposed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intervened as a barrier, between the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence the saying in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayona Alganami","text_ar":"بَيْنَ الغَنَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna yufar~iEu","text_ar":"كَانَ يُفَرِّعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was making a separation between the sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"IAth says that Hr has mentioned it as with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but, he adds, Aboo-Moosà says, it is one of his mistakes. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^aw~alu SayodK faraEahu","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَوَّلُ صَيْدٍ فَرَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is the first object of the chase of which he shed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has shed, the blood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See also 4.]) ―         -b2-  See also 8.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEa AlA^aroDa","text_ar":"فَرَعَ الاَرْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 4.       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariEa","text_ar":"فَرِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":",] (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEN","text_ar":"فَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, abundant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from deficiency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of the hair"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K, TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aforaEu","text_ar":"اَفْرَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["O","TA","K","S"]},{"entry_id":"n33616","headword_ar":"فَرْعٌ","root":"frE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything; (S, O, Msb, K;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroE","text_ar":"فَرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what branches forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yatafar~aEu","text_ar":"يَتَفَرَّعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the lower,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest, part"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwEN","text_ar":"فُرُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only. (TA.) It is said in a trad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~u Al$~ajari A^aboEadu mina AlxaArifi qaAluwA faroEuhaA","text_ar":"اَىُّ الشَّجَرِ اَبْعَدُ مِنَ الخَارِفِ قَالُوا فَرْعُهَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAla waka*`lika AlS~af~u AlA^aw~alu","text_ar":"قَالَ وَكَذٰلِكَ الصَّفُّ الاَوَّلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What part of trees is furthest from the plucker of the fruit? they said, The uppermost part thereof; he said, And such like is the first row"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the persons worshipping in the mosque]. (TA.) Thus"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEu AlA^u*uni","text_ar":"فَرْعُ الاُذُنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, part of the ear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * MF, TA;) pl. as above. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwEu","text_ar":"فُرُوعُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuqolatayoni","text_ar":"المُقْلَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The upper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uppermost, parts of the two eyeballs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A branch of a tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(KL, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head of a branch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great branch:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a branch of anything."},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA.) ―         -b3-  [And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A branch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"subdivision,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"derivative,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything that is regarded as a fundamental or a whole;]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing that is built,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"founded, upon another thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSolN","text_ar":"اَصْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) [the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuwEN","text_ar":"فُرُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSuwlN","text_ar":"اُصُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning “ fundamentals, ” signifies, in the conventional language of the lawyers and the men of science in general, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"derivative institutes of the law,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see 2:]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu","text_ar":"عِلْمُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuruwEi","text_ar":"الفُرُوعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the science of the derivative institutes of the law"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is what is commonly known by the appellation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eilomu Alfiqohi","text_ar":"عِلْمُ الفِقْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the science of jurisprudence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is mainly concerned with institutes derived from fundamentals]. (Hájjee Khaleefeh.) ―         -b4-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a woman: pl. as above [app. used in a collective sense like the French “ cheveux ”]: (K, TA:) one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tawiylapu AlfuruwEi","text_ar":"طَوِيلَةُ الفُرُوعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A long-haired woman"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And (K) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Full"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abundant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA.) ―         -b5-  And (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man of eminence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people or party: (S, O, K, TA:) pl. as above: (TA:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa faroEu qawomihi","text_ar":"هُوَ فَرْعُ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"man of eminence, of his people"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, TA, *) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino furuwEihim","text_ar":"مِنْ فُرُوعِهِم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of their nobles,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And [app. from the same word as signifying “ a branch of a tree, ”] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A valley branching off."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A channel in which water runs to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iEob","text_ar":"شِعْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) i. e. the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAdiY","text_ar":"وَادِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"water-course in a low tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the two acclivities of two mountains"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [but] in this sense its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firaAEN","text_ar":"فِرَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, TA.)       -A2-  Also [or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN faroEN","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bow that is made from the extreme portion of a branch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, O, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the head thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA:) and (K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bow that is not"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made from a branch"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divided lengthwise"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA) is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, TA;) such as is [made from a branch] divided lengthwise being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"filoqN","text_ar":"فِلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroE","text_ar":"فَرْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the best of bows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn, K, TA:) and [this word is used as an epithet, i. e.] one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawosN faroEN","text_ar":"قَوْسٌ فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEapN","text_ar":"فَرْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A3-  Also, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Property that is beneficial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"serviceable, and made ready,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prepared:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA:) or, accord. to the S, it is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEN","text_ar":"فَرَعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"which has this signification; but this is said by Sgh [app. in the TS], and after him by the author of the K, to be a mistake; and a verse in which it occurs with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent is cited in the O and K as an ex. of it in this sense: it may be, however, that the poet has made the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent of necessity [by poetic license, for the sake of the metre]; or it may here [properly] signify “ a branch, ” and be metonymically used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"recent property."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A4-  See also the next paragraph, latter half."}],"source_refs":["Msb","KL","TA","K","S","O","As","AHn"]},{"entry_id":"n33617","headword_ar":"فَرَعٌ","root":"frE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firstling of the camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which they used to sacrifice to their gods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"looking for a blessing thereby;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEapN","text_ar":"فَرَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (Mgh, Msb:) hence, (Mgh, O, K,) it is said in a trad., [implying the prohibition of this custom,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA faraEa","text_ar":"لَا فَرَعَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA EatiyrapN","text_ar":"وَلَا عَتِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, *) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walaA Eatiyrapa","text_ar":"وَلَا عَتِيرَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA faraEapa","text_ar":"لَا فَرَعَةَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh: [see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EatiyrapN","text_ar":"عَتِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when the camels amounted to the number for which their owner wished, they sacrificed"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a firstling"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or when one's camels amounted to a complete hundred, (K, TA,) he sacrificed a he-camel thereof every year, and gave it to the people to eat, neither he nor his family tasting it, or rather, it is said, (TA,) he sacrificed a young, or youthful, he-camel to his idol: and"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2380},{"kind":"text","text":"the Muslims used to do it in the first part of ElIslám: then it was abrogated: (K, TA:) accord. to the Bári' and the Mj, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"firstling of camels"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that of sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats"},{"kind":"text","text":"are thus called: (Msb:) the pl. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEN","text_ar":"فَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furuEN","text_ar":"فُرُعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with two dammehs. (K.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aw~alu AlS~ayodi","text_ar":"اَوَّلُ الصَّيْدِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEN","text_ar":"فَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The first of what are taken by the chase"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like is a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frE","text_ar":"فرع"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as being likened to a firstling: so says Yezeed Ibn-Murrah. (TA. [See Freytag's Arab. Prov., i. 35.]) ―         -b2-  The poet Ows Ibn- Hajar, (S, O,) or Bishr Ibn-Abee-Kházim, has used it as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"skin of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraE","text_ar":"فَرَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O; *) suppressing the prefix"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jilod","text_ar":"جِلْد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) for they used to clothe with its skin another young one of a camel, in order that the mother of the one sacrificed might incline to it [and yield her milk]. (O; and the like is said in the TA.)       -A2-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small lice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one thereof"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEapN","text_ar":"فَرَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEapN","text_ar":"فَرْعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or, accord. to some,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"frEp","text_ar":"فرعة"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large louse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A3-  And the former ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faraEN","text_ar":"فَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Food that is prepared"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for persons invited to partake of it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the occasion of camels' bringing forth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xurosN","text_ar":"خُرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies such as is on the occasion of a woman's bringing forth. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A portion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"share;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qisomN","text_ar":"قِسْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K, TA:) accord. to some, peculiarly"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faroEN","text_ar":"فَرْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last quarter.       -A4-  It is also the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fariEa","text_ar":"فَرِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. [See 1, last sentence.])"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","L","TA"]}]}}